We will only use any information we collect about you lawfully, in accordance with the Data Protection Act 1998.IP addresses An IP address is a unique identifier given to you by your internet provider when you connect online.
We use these addresses to track your movements and look at trends, such as geographical location, which helps us track our readers, produce better statistics and improve our quality of service.
IP addresses are not linked to personally identifiable information.
We will not share IP addresses with anyone else, unless we believe said IP address is from a user who we have reason to believe is breaking the law.

Cookies We may use a cookie to record a user's preferences to make it easier to access eSports News UK in the future.
Your privacy is not compromised, because the cookie is stored on the user's computer.
You can deactivate cookies in your web browser, or even block cookies.
